title: Supertramp-Crime of the Century MFSL audiophile vinyl rip
description:
This was transcribed from an early version of the half-speed MFSL LP using a Lyra Helikon SL turntable, a $15,000 custom built tube phono stage (that bettered and replaced the Aesthetix Io Signature stage) into a Yamaha CD-recorder acting as the A/D converter. The turntable and all electronics were sited on performance enhancing Sonority shelving (very inert dense cast acrylic). All electronics were also fed pure balanced power via a 300 lb Equitech wall transformer. 

I also have the MFSL Ultradisk CD here to compare this transcription with-and there is no comparison. Which is why this is the version I am uploading-vinyl noise and all!
